<h2 id="math">Math mode</h2>
<p>Math mode is a special markup mode that is used to typeset mathematical
formulas. It is entered by wrapping an equation in <code>$</code> characters. This works
both in markup and code. The equation will be typeset into its own block if it
starts and ends with at least one space (e.g. <code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span> x<span class="typ-math-op">^</span>2 <span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code>). Inline math can be
produced by omitting the whitespace (e.g. <code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>x<span class="typ-math-op">^</span>2<span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code>). An overview over the
syntax specific to math mode follows:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Example</th><th>See</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr><td>Inline math</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>x<span class="typ-math-op">^</span>2<span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/math/">Math</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>Block-level math</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span> x<span class="typ-math-op">^</span>2 <span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/math/">Math</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>Bottom attachment</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>x<span class="typ-math-op">_</span>1<span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/math/attach/"><code>attach</code></a></td></tr>
<tr><td>Top attachment</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>x<span class="typ-math-op">^</span>2<span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/math/attach/"><code>attach</code></a></td></tr>
<tr><td>Fraction</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>1 + <span class="typ-punct">(</span>a+b<span class="typ-punct">)</span><span class="typ-math-op">/</span>5<span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/math/frac/"><code>frac</code></a></td></tr>
<tr><td>Line break</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>x <span class="typ-escape">\</span> y<span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/text/linebreak/" title="`linebreak`"><code>linebreak</code></a></td></tr>
<tr><td>Alignment point</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>x <span class="typ-math-op">&amp;</span>= 2 <span class="typ-escape">\</span> <span class="typ-math-op">&amp;</span>= 3<span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/math/">Math</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>Variable access</td><td><code><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span><span class="typ-pol">#</span><span class="typ-pol">x</span><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span>, <span class="typ-math-delim">$</span><span class="typ-pol">pi</span><span class="typ-math-delim">$</span></code></td><td><a href="/docs/reference/math/">Math</a></td></tr>
